gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 113, Kings 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Chicago Bulls complete the comeback with a 22-7 run down the stretch to defeat the Sacramento Kings, 113-109. For Chicago, Coby White led the way with a career-high 37 points, five rebounds, and seven assists while aided by DeMar DeRozan (33 points (19 in the fourth), four assists) and Ayo Dosunmu (20 points, five assists) in the victory. De’Aaron Fox tallied 20 points and 10 assists with Domantas Sabonis recording 18 points and 21 rebounds for Sacramento in the losing effort. Chicago improves to 29-32 on the season, while Sacramento moves to 34-26 with the loss.
